content: The interactive map is great. But there is no way to reset the data if you want to start over. Additionally, it lacks a list of side quests.
Good for recipes and armor checklist, but the map lags if you use it for anything other than the towers. Not very useful when the thing you'll need it for the most is the 900 Korok seeds.

replyContent: Thank you for your feedback. Can you please share the problem with us in more detail so that we can improve our app. Please contact us at support@redstart.io, use the feedback link in the app, or let us know here.

content: Excellent app, just a couple of suggestions: 1. When I click a shrine from the map, it would be helpful to know if it requires a quest or a particular method to unlock it. 2. Being able to individually select which "mini-boss" I'd like to view on the map rather than all at once. Apart from them two minor issues, thoroughly pleased with the app and worth every penny üëç

If this app had a cloud backup of the user data and more map options (like treasure locations, goddess statues, side quests etc) it would be the best available. By far! It already has the best design and smoothness. But it lacks some important features.

This has great information in a pleasing ui. Really good for completionists, as you can tick off which locations you have done. Includes korok seed and mini boss locations. Cooking simulator is handy too.

Absolutely must have. You didnt have any reviews but you deserve it. This app is amazing, especially for cooking. The map and filters are very well done and it includes everything you could possibly need. Well worth the money!

I loved the website and I'm loving the app! Thank you for bringing it to the App Store and Google Play! By far the best quick-reference guide for this game. My only suggestion would be to add an anchor link in the compendium to places on the map. For example, horses are found in Hyrule Field, so tapping on "Hyrule Field" would take you to Hyrule Field on the map.
